A moment in the life of Mauz. In case you’re my actual friend in real life and you’re always wondering why I never text back… this is why… this is what I’m doing. All day, I’m moming so hard and when I’m not moming and I’m working on whatever company it is I’m focused on at that moment, I’m wishing I was moming. I can’t wait to be able to sit down in our mini classroom and teach this tiny human about the world. I am in complete disbelief that one day, when I was 20 years old, I said I would never ever ever have a child. 10 years later (and somewhat wiser), it ended up being all I wanted. Who would have guessed it to be, quite literally, the best thing to ever happen to me?… 😍

2023 brought me my first panic attack where I was trapped in a car for almost 4 hours in 108 degree weather with no water, only 8 minutes from my house. I had no one to call. No one I could tell my worries to. No one to burden. I have all these wonderful people around me who would listen, but I felt 110% alone in a split second. I couldn’t wrap my head around who to even call. In reality, I didn’t want to call anyone. Stuck in parking lot of an abandoned building where I could pull off the road, my life completely crumbled. My vision lagged and my brain could not stop screaming at me yet it was utterly silent and blank. I could not breathe. I could not dial 911. My world just stopped…

And then… at what I felt was rock bottom with nothing to lose, I did something that would shock anyone I’ve ever known. I needed to try something else because nothing previously worked for me, I owed it to myself to take it seriously. I turned to God. I started going to church every Sunday, or I watched the @illuminatecommunity stream from home. Weeks went by and not much changed… I had 3 more panic attacks on a much smaller scale. But, then… months went by and I started to realize that my life wasn’t all black anymore. I saw color, I saw beauty in simplicity again. I wanted less, and by wanting less I gained so much more. I began to actually believe that life doesn’t have to be a spiral at different paces all the time. The cup doesn’t have to be half empty if I choose so. Life gets so much brighter without hanging onto the past: the mistakes, the regrets, the people, the trauma, the hate, the disappointment. In the end - the saying “give it to God” exists for a reason… 💕
